Step 1: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
• From the balance sheet, total liabilities are given as Total Current Liabilities = 1,548,001.20 and total assets are 15,653,266.97.  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 1,548,001.20 / 15,653,266.97 ≈ 0.0989, which rounds to 0.10.

Step 2: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 2,620,023.09 and Total Revenue = 5,760,023.09.  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100% = (2,620,023.09 / 5,760,023.09) × 100% ≈ 45.45%.

Step 3: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 803,237.11.  
• Using the current liabilities of 1,548,001.20 from the balance sheet as the denominator, the ratio is:  
 Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities = 803,237.11 / 1,548,001.20 ≈ 0.5187, which rounds to 0.52.

Thus, the solution is:
